FT  02 MAR 94 / International Company News: Union Pacific buys oil and gas
assets for Dollars 819m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Union Pacific, the US railroad and resources group, has agreed to pay
Dollars 819m for the oil and gas interests of Cypress Amax, the mining
company formed by a merger late last year.
Union said it had already reached agreement to sell some assets for Dollars
94.5m, retaining mainly gas producing, gathering and processing assets in
Texas and Louisiana.
The disposal signals Cypress Amax's intention to concentrate on its mining
activities. It brings Union Pacific proven gas reserves to 550bn cubic feet,
adding approximately 20 per cent to its existing reserves.
In addition, the assets purchased include 550 miles of gathering lines and
three gas processing plants. Union Pacific said that the properties it was
acquiring were underdeveloped, and that it planned to begin drilling by the
middle of this year to add to the proven reserves in the field.
Union said the proven reserves accounted for Dollars 424m of the purchase
price, with the pipelines and other assets making up the rest.
