<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Share placing values Cedardata at Pounds
32.2m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Cedardata, the Surrey-based accounting and financial management
software group, which is coming to market through a share placing, have been
priced at 105p valuing the group at Pounds 32.2m.
The company is best known for its modular Cfacs (Commercial and Financial
Accounts Systems) accounting software, which was launched in 1987 and now
has a strong blue-chip customer base.
Since the launch of Cfacs, turnover and profits have grown rapidly. Pre-tax
profits before non-recurring items, have risen from Pounds 430,000 in 1991
to a forecast Pounds 2.65m for the year to the end of March. Earnings of
6.1p per share are forecast, up from 4.2p last year.
As part of the placing of 13.7m shares, representing 44.75 per cent of the
enlarged ordinary share capital, the group is issuing 1.43m new shares to
raise funds for the development of Cfacs. The issue is sponsored by Greig
Middleton and the shares are due to begin trading on March 7.
</TEXT>
