<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 94 / Colleges claim victory in dispute
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Further education college employers yesterday claimed victory in their
dispute with the Natfhe lecturers' union over new contracts, after the union
announced it was abandoning national negotiations in favour of local
bargaining, John Authers writes.
About 100 Natfhe members who disobeyed union orders yesterday by holding
unofficial strikes, also face possible damages and disciplinary action from
college principals.
The Court of Appeal last week ruled that Natfhe's national strike called for
yesterday was unlawful because college principals had not been given names
of all the union members balloted.
Lecturers are in dispute with the Colleges' Employers' Forum over new
contracts which would halve their annual holiday leave and add an hour to
the working day.
