FT  02 MAR 94 / Number of companies entering receivership jumps
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of companies entering receivership or administration jumped by
more than 50 per cent to 248 last month, according to figures from the
official London and Edinburgh Gazettes analysed by accountants Touche Ross.
The total for the first two months of the year was 411, compared with 772
for the same period last year.
Mr Christopher Morris, head of insolvency at Touche, said the monthly rise
might have been exceptional but possibly suggested that bankers were
starting to worry about the chances of their customers being able to trade
successfully out of recession.
