received more than 6,000 pages of documents. These reveal on inspection that
the gerrymandering went far beyond homes for votes.'
The further allegations cover land disposals, disposals of property and
planning decisions according to Mr Coleman. He added: 'We have asked the
district auditor for assurances that he will be addressing these issues.'
