<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Coffee and cocoa steady - Market
Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London Commodity Exchange COCOA and COFFEE futures showed steady gains
yesterday after Monday's sharp declines, but traders described trading as
'unenthusiastic'. May delivery cocoa ended Pounds 7 up at 917 a tonne after
dipping to Pounds 905 early on. Most traders thought support at Pounds 900
was likely to hold, though some thought a slide to Pounds 870 possible
unless fresh outright buying returned.
The coffee market enjoyed light support from a further drop in US certified
stocks and the May price closed at Dollars 1,223 a tonne, up Dollars 10.
At the London Metal Exchange COPPER set a generally lower tone.
