<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 94 / UK Company News: ITV companies to merge sales
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Carlton Communications says it intends to integrate its airtime sales
operation with that of Central. The move marks the start of reorganisations
among advertising sales houses following the series of ITV company mergers.
The new sales operation following Carlton's takeover of Central will be led
by Mr Martin Bowley, sales director of Carlton Television.
Until now, Central's airtime has been sold by TSMS, a joint venture with
Anglia Television. But Anglia in turn has been acquired by MAI, which
controls Meridian Broadcasting, the ITV company for the south of England.
The Department of Trade and Industry has insisted as a condition of agreeing
to the takeovers without a reference to the Monopolies and Mergers
Commission that no sales house should have more than 25 per cent of the
television advertising market.
