FT  01 MAR 94 / International Company News: Aetna hit by claims from
California earthquake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Aetna, the US composite insurer, warned yesterday the southern Californian
earthquake and winter storms would cost it Dollars 120m or Dollars 1.07 a
share in the current quarter.
The company put its losses from the earthquake at Dollars 80m, making it one
of the largest losses yet announced by a US insurer.
In all, the cost to the insurance industry of the earthquake is expected to
reach Dollars 2.5bn.
The expected earthquake losses, which are after reinsurance and tax,
resulted from 2,500 claims in the affected area, the company said.
It added that it expected to receive 31,000 claims from the winter storms of
January and early February, with net losses put at Dollars 40m.
As a result of these first-quarter items, Aetna said it would drop its
earnings forecast for the year to Dollars 5.65 a share, from Dollars 6.50 a
share.
