<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Raglan issue increases portfolio
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Raglan Property Trust, the property development and investment company, is
reinvesting the bulk of the proceeds from its recent rights issue in the
Pounds 16.5m acquisition of a portfolio of retail and office properties.
Raglan announced a 2-for-1 rights issue in November, raising Pounds 19m for
'selective property investment'. The new portfolio has a broad spread of
locations, and offers an initial yield of more than 9 per cent.
The company is emerging from four years of losses.
Raglan now has a portfolio of properties with a book value of about Pounds
50m, while net debt is approximately Pounds 22m. The management said it
would be happy with a higher level of gearing.
It aims to build up its rental portfolio, providing cash to channel into its
core property development. This is a 223,000 sq ft site in Banbury, which
will be developed into a town centre shopping mall.
</TEXT>
