<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAR 94 / UK Company News: ICS rises 10.5% to Pounds 2.62m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Industrial Control Services Group, the electronic safety systems
manufacturer, yesterday reported a 10.5 per cent increase in interim pre-tax
profits despite difficult economic conditions in its markets, particularly
the oil sector.
Profits were Pounds 2.62m (Pounds 2.37m) for the six months to November 30
on turnover up 33 per cent to Pounds 39.9m (Pounds 30.1m) reflecting strong
growth in control systems and the impact of the Brisco acquisition.
Earnings per share slipped to 2.91p (3.82p) through the dilution from the
joint venture with Elsag Bailey. However, interim dividend is being
increased to 1.5p (1.33p).
Operating profits increased 32 per cent to Pounds 3.6m (Pounds 2.73m) but
the gain was partly offset by Pounds 546,000 costs associated with ICS
ending manufacturing in Scotland under its rationalisation programme.
The control systems grew strongly with turnover more than doubled to Pounds
18.2m (Pounds 8.5m).
</TEXT>
