FT  01 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Gartmore Scotland
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Net asset value per capital share at The Gartmore Scotland Investment Trust
rose 26 per cent from 249p to 314.5p over the six months to January 1.
Gross revenue advanced to Pounds 976,000 (Pounds 898,000) in the first half,
on the back of Pounds 119,000 (nil) coming from enhanced scrip dividends.
Interest on deposits fell to Pounds 28,000 (Pounds 68,000). Administrative
expenses rose to Pounds 191,000 (Pounds 145,000) and net revenue to Pounds
644,000 (Pounds 562,000).
Earnings were 4.76p (4.15p) per share and the second interim dividend is
held at 2.4p for a total at the halfway stage of 4.8p.
